_through_education_and_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689151332 320w" width="1500" height="1000" alt="World Youth Skills Day Empowering youth through education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="World Youth Skills Day Empowering youth through education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-19_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-a6b3" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-20_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-21_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-22_"><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-23_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-25_">In 2014, the United Nations General Assembly declared the 15th of July as World Youth Skills Day. This annual event aims to address unemployment and underemployment challenges by striving for better socio-economic conditions for today's youth. World Youth Skills Day focuses on a specific theme to illuminate critical issues and promote practical solutions each year.<br><br>In this article, we will discuss the transformative power of education and training in empowering youth and the role played by teacher and trainer in shaping our youth’s employability skills.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-26_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-28_">Skilling teachers, trainers, and youth for a transformative future</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Skilling_teachers_trainers_and_youth_for_a_transformative_future_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151747" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Skilling_teachers_trainers_and_youth_for_a_transformative_future_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151747 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Skilling_teachers_trainers_and_youth_for_a_transformative_future_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689151747 320w" width="3420" height="2280" alt="Skilling teachers, trainers, and youth for a transformative future - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Skilling teachers, trainers, and youth for a transformative future - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-29_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-30_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-32_">This year’s theme is "Skilling teachers, trainers, and youth for a transformative future." This highlights the essential role played by teachers, trainers, and educators in providing skills for young individuals to transition into the labour market.
<br><br>As a <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/uk-accredited-statutory-and-mandatory-training-providers-about-us" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">training provider</span></i></a>, we believe in the power of education and training to transform lives. We aim to help those entering the workforce to develop <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/employability-skills-training-courses-online" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">employability skills</span></i></a>. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-33_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-35_">The essential role of teachers, trainers, and educators </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_essential_role_of_teachers_trainers_and_educators_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151863" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_essential_role_of_teachers_trainers_and_educators_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151863 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_essential_role_of_teachers_trainers_and_educators_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689151863 320w" width="4600" height="3070" alt="The essential role of teachers, trainers, and educators - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The essential role of teachers, trainers, and educators - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-36_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-37_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-39_">In today's world, young individuals require agile and adaptable skill sets, characterised by technological advancements and shifting labour market dynamics. Education and training play a pivotal role in supporting youth employment, providing young individuals with the right opportunities to learn and develop economic benefits. Technical and vocational education and training (TVET) are well-positioned to meet these demands. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-40_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-42_">Empowering youth through technical and vocational education and training (TVET)</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_youth_through_technical_and_vocational_education_and_training_TVET_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151993" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_youth_through_technical_and_vocational_education_and_training_TVET_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689151993 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_youth_through_technical_and_vocational_education_and_training_TVET_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689151993 320w" width="2545" height="1697" alt="Empowering youth through technical and vocational education and training (TVET) - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empowering youth through technical and vocational education and training (TVET) - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-43_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-44_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-46_">Technical and vocational education and training (TVET) focuses on providing affordable quality education and developing technical and vocational skills for employment, decent work, and entrepreneurship. It aims to eliminate gender disparity, ensure access for the vulnerable, and address the multiple demands of an economic, social, and environmental nature.<br><br>TVET equips youth with the skills required to access the world of work, including skills for self-employment. It enhances responsiveness to changing skill demands, increases productivity, and raises wage levels. Moreover, TVET reduces access barriers to work through work-based learning and offers skill development opportunities for low-skilled and underemployed individuals.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-47_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-49_">Eye-opening statistics: Challenges in youth employment and education</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Eye-opening_statistics_Challenges_in_youth_employment_and_education_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689152127" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Eye-opening_statistics_Challenges_in_youth_employment_and_education_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689152127 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Eye-opening_statistics_Challenges_in_youth_employment_and_education_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689152127 320w" width="2850" height="1900" alt="Eye-opening statistics Challenges in youth employment and education - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Eye-opening statistics Challenges in youth employment and education - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-50_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-51_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding the significance of World Youth Skills Day requires us to acknowledge several eye-opening facts from the International Labour Organisation:</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-53_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-54_">The youth population grew by 139 million between 1997 and 2017, while the youth labour force decreased by 58.7 million, with more young individuals favouring to stay in school. </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-56_">Globally, one in five young people is NEET (Not in Employment, Education, or Training), representing millions of young individuals without a job or educational opportunities.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-58_">On average, young people wait 13.8 months to secure a stable or satisfactory job, reflecting the challenges of transitioning from education to the workforce. </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-60_">In emerging and developing economies, almost two out of five young workers live on less than US$3.10 daily. </li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-62_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-64_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Youth_Skills_Day_Empowering_youth_through_education_and_training_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689152680" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Youth_Skills_Day_Empowering_youth_through_education_and_training_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1689152680 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Youth_Skills_Day_Empowering_youth_through_education_and_training_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1689152680 320w" width="3096" height="2064" alt="World Youth Skills Day Empowering youth through education and training - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="World Youth Skills Day Empowering youth through education and training - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-65_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-66_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-68_">World Youth Skills Day serves as a platform to recognise the transformative power of education and training in shaping the future of young individuals. We can empower them to contribute to a prosperous and sustainable world by providing them with the skills and support they need. <br><br>As a leading e-learning training provider across multiple sectors, we at The <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Mandatory Training Group</span></i></a> offers a range of courses to support young employees entering the workforce. We believe in providing accessible and comprehensive online training opportunities that equip young individuals with the knowledge and skills needed to excel in their roles. Together, we can all commit to a future where every young person has access to quality education, lifelong learning opportunities, and a pathway to success. <br><br><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/employability-skills-training-courses-online?sort_by=title-ascending" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Click here</span></i></a> to see our wide range of employability skills courses and training programmes to help you develop your professional skills.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-69_ pf-r pf-r-eh pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-70_"><div data-pf-type="Slideshow" class="sc-furwcr jFnGOX pf-71_"><div data-id="slider-adc2a6c9-ab76-4da6-b323-a92287f48dd4-all" class="pf-slider scrollfix"><div class="pf-slide"><div style="display:block" class="sc-fIITEw glyLTg pf-72_" data-pf-type="SlideshowSlide"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-73_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-74_"><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-GEbAx gWfVlz pf-75_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/nhscareerslogo-1671516106607.png?v=1671516190" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/nhscareerslogo-1671516106607.png?v=1671516190 1536w" width="134" height="